# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Environment variables for bloomagain-admin
#
# Split:
#   • NEXT_PUBLIC_* — baked into the client JS bundle at build time. These
#     ARE in the public bundle (visible in DevTools), so committing isn't
#     dangerous, but we still don't commit them because real values would
#     drift across environments. Copy this file to .env.production locally
#     before `firebase deploy --only hosting`.
#
#   • Server-only vars (BACKEND_*, BLOOMAGAIN_*, NICE_*) — referenced by
#     Next.js API routes at runtime. These must NOT live in any committed
#     file. They are set directly on the Cloud Run service that Firebase
#     Hosting frameworks-support deploys (`ssrbloomagainkorea`):
#
#       gcloud run services update ssrbloomagainkorea \
#         --region asia-northeast3 \
#         --project bloomagain-korea \
#         --update-env-vars KEY=VAL,...
#
#     (Or via the GCP Console → Cloud Run → service → Edit & Deploy New
#     Revision → Variables & Secrets.) Long-term, move BACKEND_API_KEY into
#     GCP Secret Manager and reference it from Cloud Run.
#
# For local development:
#   • Copy to .env.local with both public + server-side values filled in.
#   • Both files are gitignored.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Client (public — bundled into JS) ────────────────────────────────────────
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=bloomagain-korea.firebaseapp.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=bloomagain-korea
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=bloomagain-korea.firebasestorage.app
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID=

# ── Server-only (set on Cloud Run; do NOT put real values here) ──────────────
# BLOOMAGAIN_BACKEND_URL=https://bloomagain-backend-api-<id>.<region>.run.app
# NICE upstream: since 2026-07-04 this points at the MAIN backend's /api/v1
# (it serves /api/v1/nice/* with session→user binding). The old separate
# bloomagain-nice-backend service is legacy — only repoint back to it as an
# emergency rollback (see bloomagain-backend docs/ops-runbook.md → "NICE
# 본인인증 init fails"). Keep the /api/v1 suffix.
# NICE_BACKEND_URL=https://bloomagain-backend-api-<id>.<region>.run.app/api/v1
# BACKEND_APP_ID=<app id registered on backend>
# BACKEND_API_KEY=<secret — Secret Manager recommended>
